    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>Last updated: February 15, 2026</p>

    <div class="card">
        <p><strong>Kiso Integrity Checker</strong> (developed by <strong>Ingsha</strong> at <strong>Kiso Labs</strong>) is built as a tool to verify device security status.</p>

        <h2>1. Information Collection and Use</h2>
        <p>To provide the integrity check service, this app utilizes the <strong>Google Play Integrity API</strong>. This API may collect and send certain device information to Google, including:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Device hardware and software details (Model, Brand, Android Version).</li>
            <li>App licensing and installation metadata.</li>
            <li>Information about the device's security environment (root status, bootloader status).</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. Data Handling</h2>
        <p>We do not collect or store your personal data on our own servers. The information gathered by the Play Integrity API is processed by Google to generate a security verdict, which is displayed locally on your device in the <strong>Detailed Results</strong> section.</p>

        <h2>3. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>This app uses third-party services that may collect information used to identify you:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">Google Play Services</a></li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have any questions or suggestions about this Privacy Policy, do not hesitate to contact <strong>Ingsha</strong> at: <br>
        <strong>ingshalimbu09@gmail.com</strong></p>
    </div>

